<br>
Did not help to find the machine Aaluvasi was using did not have Kunark on it. Stuck in the middle of a higher level zone is not my idea of a picnic! But I did discover a possible safe point in the Dreadlands (assuming this because that's where I ended up). Loc is 0.00, 0.00 by the way <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . And had to wait for the others to turn up.<br>
<br>
Also, it didn't help that I did not know exactly how we were going to get there &amp; the lag was phenomenal in the forest in one of the zones (don't know which), so Chromehammer &amp; myself occassionally <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  got left behind. SO getting there was slower than anticipated, sorry guys.<br>
<br>
As the others have said, it was fun &amp; educational, even the 2 deaths (well maybe not the 2 deaths). <br>
<br>
What was more interesting was the corpse run from Dreadlands (?). Fighting it out with Llainya &amp; Chromehammer when Llainya remembered (we had been evaced when the spiders attacked) that if you got killed in a duel you don't get exp loss &amp; (more importantly) get back to your bind point (which was just outside the zone). Much faster &amp; less fraught than trying to run all the way. Chromey had some fun watching 2 naked female wood elf rangers fighting. Llainya had to zone because an Iksar Manslayer started to attack (exp loss of course if killed by mob).<br>
<br>
With some underhand tactics (i.e. spells) I nearly had Chromehammer! But I got distracted by a Iksar Manslayer (that's my story) &amp; Chromehammer was able finish me off. Llainya was able to kill the seriously wounded Chromehammer &amp; then get killed by an obliging <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  fellow player. All 3 of us got back to our bind point, tried to recover our corpses, got killed again &amp; discovered that the mob was hovering around the corpses. Gemtun &amp; Gladriel were checking periodically whilst waiting for a high level player, Darvin, a level 55+ warrior (Myrmidon) dwarf to arrive &amp; assist us. He easily vanquished the prowling beasts, we were able to loot our corpses &amp; Gemtun transported us all to WC.<br>
<br>
Wish I had evac or gate spells <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  even levitate! Hmmm, maybe I should kill Quillmane &amp; get the cloak so I can levitate! But Rangers get levitate at 39 so maybe I can wait. <br>
<br>
Thanks for the bind  at West Freeport, Gladriel<br>
<br>
Twas good to group with all of you.<br>
<br>
Luni count me in again once you've worked out what we must do besides making sure we can evac as required <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
